1
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:06,941
⟨Luna, a literature geek, and Ryoko, a full-time housewife⟩

2
00:00:07,008 --> 00:00:10,444
⟨The two get involved in incidents wherever they go.→

3
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:14,448
I solved the problem with my literary knowledge with friends I met in Osaka ⟩

4
00:00:14,515 --> 00:00:16,951
(Luna) We are connected.

5
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:20,454
⟨A new challenge: finding the password for my father's computer⟩

6
00:00:20,521 --> 00:00:23,958
(Ryoko) I guess there was some meaning in entrusting it to mom.

7
00:00:24,024 --> 00:00:26,460
⟨Ryoko has family troubles...⟩

8
00:00:26,527 --> 00:00:28,963
(Kikuo) I want to quit university. (Ryoko) What?!

9
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:31,465
⟨And a boy who behaves inexplicably →

10
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:34,034
We're going to cause trouble tonight⟩

11
00:00:41,542 --> 00:00:43,477
(knock)

12
00:00:43,544 --> 00:00:48,048
(Ryoko) Yoshika What's wrong? Did something happen?

13
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:53,554
Hey, let's talk properly?

14
00:00:56,057 --> 00:01:00,494
(Yoshika) ＼It's my life, so let me decide! /

15
00:01:00,561 --> 00:01:04,432
(Kikuo) It's not something you can easily decide based on temporary emotions!

16
00:01:04,498 --> 00:01:06,434
There are many things you can gain from university.

17
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:08,936
So please discuss it with your family...

18
00:01:09,003 --> 00:01:11,439
(Yoshika) ＼Even if I talk to them, they won't understand! /

19
00:01:11,505 --> 00:01:13,941
(Kikuo) ＼Fragrance! /

20
00:01:14,008 --> 00:01:17,511
(Ryoko) ＼Maybe we should give it some time.／

21
00:01:19,013 --> 00:01:21,449
(Baburi's voice) My parents used their money to send me to higher education →

22
00:01:21,515 --> 00:01:24,452
It's a luxury.

23
00:01:24,518 --> 00:01:26,454
(Tamura) Around that age→

24
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:29,957
I can't explain my feelings this well.

25
00:01:30,024 --> 00:01:32,460
When I told my parents that I also wanted to go to university in Osaka →

26
00:01:32,526 --> 00:01:34,962
Well, I had a hard time.

27
00:01:35,029 --> 00:01:39,467
(Luna) There are as many problems in parent-child relationships as there are families.

28
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:42,470
(Tamura) Ah, now that I think about it, what happened to your father's PC?

29
00:01:42,536 --> 00:01:46,974
(Luna) I'm tired of being burdened with troubles that I haven't opened up to yet.

30
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:49,977
(Ryoko) I mean, Tamura-san is always here.

31
00:01:50,044 --> 00:01:52,980
(Tamura) Huh? (Bubbly) Do you have free time?

32
00:01:53,047 --> 00:01:54,482
(Tamura) No…｡

33
00:01:54,548 --> 00:01:58,486
(Luna) The Metropolitan Police Department's First Investigative Division is the elite of the elite.

34
00:01:58,552 --> 00:02:00,988
One person is thrown into the elite group with high pride→

35
00:02:01,055 --> 00:02:04,925
I feel lonely because I can't find anyone to open up to →

36
00:02:04,992 --> 00:02:07,428
...I guess it's something like that.

37
00:02:07,495 --> 00:02:10,431
(Tamura) That's a strange feeling. (Bubbly) It's a star.

38
00:02:10,498 --> 00:02:12,433
Mom, you have amazing reasoning skills.

39
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,935
(Tamura) Well, we're friends, so we understand, right?

40
00:02:15,002 --> 00:02:17,438
(Luna) Hey friend...

41
00:02:17,505 --> 00:02:20,441
(Tamura) It's really unpleasant, so be careful.

42
00:02:20,508 --> 00:02:22,943
(Luna) If you feel lonely, please come anytime.

43
00:02:23,010 --> 00:02:26,514
(Kominato) ＼It's better not to spoil it, you'll get carried away／

44
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,955
(Ryoko) What?! Mr. Kominato?

45
00:02:35,022 --> 00:02:36,957
what…? Why?

46
00:02:37,024 --> 00:02:38,959
(Luna) I've been working for you since the day before yesterday.

47
00:02:39,026 --> 00:02:40,961
(Kominato) Well, the company I was supposed to start →

48
00:02:41,028 --> 00:02:43,964
My partner ran away with his money.

49
00:02:44,031 --> 00:02:46,967
When I was at a loss, Luna picked me up.

50
00:02:47,034 --> 00:02:48,969
(Ryoko) It was difficult.

51
00:02:49,036 --> 00:02:52,673
>> I'll do my best, regardless of the rain or the wind.

52
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:55,175
I know that, Kenji Miyazawa!

53
00:02:55,242 --> 00:02:58,178
(Kominato) Hey, please have the special takoyaki. (Sakurai) Thank you.

54
00:02:58,245 --> 00:03:00,681
So do your best too.

55
00:03:00,748 --> 00:03:04,118
Ryoko fights too! (Ryoko) Aha!

56
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:06,620
How should I try my best?

57
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:09,123
(Luna) Children are afraid of being rejected by their parents.

58
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:11,625
He will accept me no matter who I am →

59
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:16,630
If you can get the young lady to believe in you, she might open up to you.

60
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:19,633
(Ryoko) That's right, thank you.

61
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:22,636
(Bubbly) I'll take it!

62
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:25,139
Ah... so fluffy!

63
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:28,275
(Sakurai) Huh? This doesn't have octopus in it though.

64
00:03:28,342 --> 00:03:30,778
Seriously?

65
00:03:30,844 --> 00:03:34,782
Ah! Yabe! I'll try again. Sorry.

66
00:03:34,848 --> 00:03:37,351
Excuse me. I'm sorry. (Ryoko) Oh, ah...｡

67
00:03:38,852 --> 00:03:41,789
This is a voluntary recall. (Luna) I apologize for the inconvenience.

68
00:03:41,855 --> 00:03:43,857
📱(vibration sound)

69
00:03:47,361 --> 00:03:49,863
(Luna) Ah, I got an appointment.

70
00:03:52,866 --> 00:03:54,802
(Kikuo) Aroma, it's late...｡

71
00:03:54,868 --> 00:03:57,805
(Atsushi) Huh! Nanami Satsuki is in danger of divorce.

72
00:03:57,871 --> 00:03:59,873
Huh?

73
00:04:03,377 --> 00:04:05,746
Satsuki-san, are you okay?

74
00:04:05,813 --> 00:04:09,249
(Atsushi) Does your father also know about Satsuki Nanami?

75
00:04:09,316 --> 00:04:12,753
I interviewed her closely when she was paired up with her mother.

76
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:15,756
Dad: Back then, he was a reporter for a sports magazine.

77
00:04:15,823 --> 00:04:17,758
Hey~｡

78
00:04:17,825 --> 00:04:19,760
Is that how you met your mother?

79
00:04:19,827 --> 00:04:24,765
Ah, that was around the time I was selected as a training athlete for the Olympics.

80
00:04:24,832 --> 00:04:26,767
They were a good pair.

81
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:29,303
Both were really lively.

82
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:31,872
(Sound of door opening) (Atsushi) Hey.

83
00:04:33,874 --> 00:04:35,809
(Ryoko) Welcome.

84
00:04:35,876 --> 00:04:37,878
>> I'm coming.

85
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:42,316
(Luna) Miss, are you okay?

86
00:04:42,383 --> 00:04:45,819
(Ryoko) Yeah, I decided to wait for him to talk.

87
00:04:45,886 --> 00:04:47,821
(Luna) I see.

88
00:04:47,888 --> 00:04:51,325
(Ryoko) We're going to the Soseki researcher's house today, right?

89
00:04:51,392 --> 00:04:54,328
(Luna) Yes, a university professor.

90
00:04:54,395 --> 00:04:58,332
(Ryoko) You said there are literary spots around here too, right?

91
00:04:58,399 --> 00:05:03,270
(Luna) Yes! Natsume Soseki's former residence The site of Natsume Sensei's home.

92
00:05:03,337 --> 00:05:04,772
(Ryoko) That's right.

93
00:05:04,838 --> 00:05:06,774
(Luna) Commonly known as the cat house.

94
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:10,277
The place where I lived for about 3 years from 1903 →

95
00:05:10,344 --> 00:05:13,781
``I am a cat'' was also written there.

96
00:05:13,847 --> 00:05:18,285
The house is no longer there, but there is a stone monument and a cat object!

97
00:05:18,352 --> 00:05:19,853
(Ryoko) Nya?

98
00:05:23,857 --> 00:05:26,293
(Ryoko) Huh? Did you just say "nya"?

99
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,295
⟨A few hours later→

100
00:05:28,362 --> 00:05:31,799
I never thought I would return home on this road with such feelings →

101
00:05:31,865 --> 00:05:34,301
I never thought of it⟩

102
00:05:34,368 --> 00:05:40,374
♪～

103
00:05:48,582 --> 00:05:50,584
(Ryoko) What happened?

104
00:05:56,523 --> 00:05:58,959
(chime)

105
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:01,462
(Intercom: Yoshizawa) Yes. (Luna) This is Nomiya.

106
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:04,531
(Intercom: Yoshizawa) Ah, yes, I have been waiting for you.

107
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:10,471
(Luna) I heard that Professor Yoshizawa was in Germany.

108
00:06:10,537 --> 00:06:14,975
(Yoshizawa) Yes, I taught at a university over there for about eight years.

109
00:06:15,042 --> 00:06:16,977
I returned to Japan four years ago.

110
00:06:17,044 --> 00:06:22,483
Japan is really nice, the food is delicious and it's safe.

111
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:26,987
Well, the security situation is a bit questionable here.

112
00:06:27,054 --> 00:06:30,491
(Ryoko) Ah, there was a rope around the park, right?

113
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:34,995
>> That's right. Apparently there was a bomb threat a few days ago.

114
00:06:35,062 --> 00:06:36,497
(Ryoko) Huh!

115
00:06:36,563 --> 00:06:40,000
>> When the police investigated, it appeared that there was no bomb →

116
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:44,004
It seems that a large amount of glass fragments came out of the sandbox.

117
00:06:44,071 --> 00:06:47,007
(Luna) A piece of glass? (Ryoko) It's dangerous.

118
00:06:47,074 --> 00:06:50,511
Has the culprit been caught? >> No, not yet.

119
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:53,447
Police have stepped up neighborhood patrols →

120
00:06:53,514 --> 00:06:55,949
It's a turbulent world.

121
00:06:56,016 --> 00:06:57,951
(Ryoko) That's scary.

122
00:06:58,018 --> 00:07:01,455
(footsteps)

123
00:07:01,522 --> 00:07:03,524
Excuse me.

124
00:07:05,526 --> 00:07:15,469
♪～

125
00:07:15,536 --> 00:07:18,038
This is my wife Satsuki.

126
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:22,976
(Satsuki) Ryoko was surprised.

127
00:07:23,043 --> 00:07:25,479
long time no see.

128
00:07:25,546 --> 00:07:27,047
(Ryoko) Yeah...｡

129
00:07:28,549 --> 00:07:30,484
(Yoshizawa) Huh?

130
00:07:30,551 --> 00:07:35,489
We used to play doubles as a pair.

131
00:07:35,556 --> 00:07:39,493
We've been together in high school, university, and the corporate world.

132
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:42,496
(Yoshizawa) Wow, what a coincidence!

133
00:07:42,563 --> 00:07:46,500
Why did you break up the pair?

134
00:07:46,567 --> 00:07:51,505
(Ryoko) I got injured and have to retire.

135
00:07:51,572 --> 00:07:56,443
(Yoshizawa) I see, that must have been a shame.

136
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:58,445
Since when have the two met again?

137
00:07:58,512 --> 00:08:01,949
(Luna) Looks delicious! I love Madeleine.

138
00:08:02,015 --> 00:08:05,452
I'll eat it. >> Please enjoy it.

139
00:08:05,519 --> 00:08:08,455
(Ryoko) I'll eat it.

140
00:08:08,522 --> 00:08:10,524
(Luna) So fluffy!

141
00:08:12,526 --> 00:08:15,529
(Yoshizawa) This is my wife's favorite.

142
00:08:18,532 --> 00:08:21,468
Hey, you sit down too.

143
00:08:21,535 --> 00:08:25,472
No, I... >> It's okay.

144
00:08:25,539 --> 00:08:28,475
In the first place, badminton is...

145
00:08:28,542 --> 00:08:32,479
(Luna) Um, I'm sorry, but what was the book you asked for?

146
00:08:32,546 --> 00:08:34,481
Sorry, I wanted to see it soon.

147
00:08:34,548 --> 00:08:38,051
>> That's right, sorry.

148
00:08:39,553 --> 00:08:41,989
(Yoshizawa) A reduced edition of ``I am a cat.''

149
00:08:42,055 --> 00:08:43,523
Are you sure this is the case?

150
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:46,526
(Luna) Yes, that's right. (Ryoko) It's small.

151
00:08:46,593 --> 00:08:49,029
>> Compact size, which was revolutionary at the time →

152
00:08:49,096 --> 00:08:52,532
It is said to have been very popular due to its highly artistic binding.

153
00:08:52,599 --> 00:08:54,968
please.

154
00:08:55,035 --> 00:08:59,973
(Luna) This is my first time seeing the real thing. How beautiful.

155
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:03,977
(Yoshizawa) It was reprinted repeatedly from the Taisho era to the early Showa era.

156
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:08,482
This is the 62nd edition, published in 1919.

157
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,484
(Ryoko) 100 years ago?

158
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:13,487
It's such a precious thing.

159
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:17,491
(Luna) Thank you very much for your kind words.

160
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:20,494
>> Please take your time today.

161
00:09:20,561 --> 00:09:23,063
I'm sure there will be some stories to come.

162
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:30,003
(Satsuki) Ryunosuke, welcome back.

163
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,005
Welcome back.

164
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:35,509
This is Luna Nomiya and Ryoko Sawatsuji.

165
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,578
(Luna) Hello. (Ryoko) Sorry to bother you.

166
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:44,518
(Luna) Does Ryunosuke have the same handwriting as Ryunosuke Akutagawa?

167
00:09:44,585 --> 00:09:46,019
>> Yes.

168
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:49,022
(Ryoko) Do you like literature?

169
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:53,026
>>I read a lot in Germany to study Japanese.

170
00:09:53,093 --> 00:09:54,528
(Ryoko) Amazing!

171
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,530
(Ryuunosuke) It's just killing time.

172
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:59,533
(Luna) It might come in handy someday.

173
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:03,036
Literature is full of all kinds of wisdom.

174
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:07,040
It's someone who will accompany you in your life.

175
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:12,045
(Ryoko) She also uses her knowledge of literature to solve mysteries.

176
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:14,114
>>The mystery of the incident...

177
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:18,552
So can you solve this mystery?

178
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:23,557
One junior high school student snatched a bag and was taken into police custody.

179
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:27,060
What I snatched was a bag full of rolls.

180
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:31,064
Why did a middle school student do such a thing?

181
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:33,133
(Yoshizawa) Ryunosuke.

182
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:45,645
Sorry, it's embarrassing.

183
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:50,584
(Luna) May I see your photo?

184
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:53,020
>> Ah yes.

185
00:10:53,086 --> 00:11:09,036
♪～

186
00:11:09,703 --> 00:11:13,140
(Luna) Ryunosuke, will you be dancing?

187
00:11:13,206 --> 00:11:17,144
>>Yes, my neighbor Koji invited me.

188
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:21,148
(Luna) Is this the girl? (Satsuki) Yes, we were best friends.

189
00:11:21,214 --> 00:11:25,652
When he first returned to Japan, he took care of Ryunosuke, who had trouble adjusting to Japanese school.

190
00:11:25,719 --> 00:11:28,655
Thank you for watching me all the time.

191
00:11:28,722 --> 00:11:31,658
(Luna) He was my best friend...

192
00:11:31,725 --> 00:11:34,161
(Yoshizawa) In the wake of Koji's junior high school entrance exam →

193
00:11:34,227 --> 00:11:37,164
Both of us have stopped dancing.

194
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:40,167
Hmm, probably here.

195
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,736
Mr. Yoshizawa...

196
00:11:48,742 --> 00:11:51,745
(chime)

197
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:57,617
(Monitor) I'm a police officer. Please let me ask you a few questions.

198
00:11:57,684 --> 00:11:59,152
You, the police.

199
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:02,155
(Monitor) This is about the bomb threat the other day.

200
00:12:02,222 --> 00:12:05,659
(Monitor) On the night of the incident, there was a boy who looked a lot like Ryunosuke →

201
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:09,162
The public phone used to make the bomb threat was said to have been used →

202
00:12:09,229 --> 00:12:11,164
There is eyewitness testimony.

203
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:20,674
♪～

204
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:24,678
Ah... I understand.

205
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:28,181
The interview is voluntary, right?

206
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:32,686
Would it be possible for me to talk to you and your family first?

207
00:12:32,753 --> 00:12:36,189
I'll be sure to contact you later.

208
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,259
(Monitor) I look forward to hearing from you.

209
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:46,266
I'll talk to Ryunosuke.

210
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:53,640
(Luna) The day there was a bomb threat →

211
00:12:53,707 --> 00:12:56,643
How was Ryunosuke?

212
00:12:56,710 --> 00:13:01,648
>> We were both away on business that day.

213
00:13:01,715 --> 00:13:06,653
My son has been a little emotionally unstable lately.

214
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:11,658
It's embarrassing, but the media has been making a fuss about the divorce crisis.

215
00:13:11,725 --> 00:13:16,163
My son was also interviewed by a weekly magazine.

216
00:13:16,229 --> 00:13:21,668
However, I don't understand the meaning of bread and meat at all.

217
00:13:21,735 --> 00:13:23,670
(Luna) Meat?

218
00:13:23,737 --> 00:13:26,673
(Yoshizawa's voice) In addition to bread, there are also blocks of pork and →

219
00:13:26,740 --> 00:13:29,676
Don't buy a lot of stuffed animals of the same shape →

220
00:13:29,743 --> 00:13:32,679
I keep throwing it away immediately.

221
00:13:32,746 --> 00:13:35,682
(Luna) Same shape...｡

222
00:13:35,749 --> 00:13:38,685
>>I'm not familiar with psychology→

223
00:13:38,752 --> 00:13:42,689
What are the possible motives for this behavior?

224
00:13:42,756 --> 00:13:45,258
I can only speculate.

225
00:13:48,261 --> 00:13:50,263
how was it?

226
00:13:51,264 --> 00:13:54,634
(Luna) He said I could talk to Mr. Nomiya and the others.

227
00:13:54,701 --> 00:13:56,203
(Ryoko) Huh?

228
00:13:58,205 --> 00:14:00,640
>> Can I make a request?

229
00:14:00,707 --> 00:14:04,711
It may be easier to talk about these things with a third party.

230
00:14:06,213 --> 00:14:09,149
(Luna) If we can help.

231
00:14:09,216 --> 00:14:11,151
>> No, but...

232
00:14:11,218 --> 00:14:13,720
(chime)

233
00:14:18,225 --> 00:14:20,227
Koji-kun?

234
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:26,666
(Koji) Sorry for the sudden change.

235
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:30,170
It's been a while. What happened?

236
00:14:30,237 --> 00:14:32,172
If you pass by→

237
00:14:32,239 --> 00:14:35,175
I heard the police say they wanted to see Ryunosuke.

238
00:14:35,242 --> 00:14:37,677
Were you here because you were worried?

239
00:14:37,744 --> 00:14:39,679
Ah... yes.

240
00:14:39,746 --> 00:14:41,681
(Satsuki) Thank you.

241
00:14:41,748 --> 00:14:46,686
Ah, Koji-kun, you cut your hair short.

242
00:14:46,753 --> 00:14:50,190
Last month, I took the plunge and became a shaved head.

243
00:14:50,257 --> 00:14:52,192
It gets in the way of studying.

244
00:14:52,259 --> 00:14:55,629
I heard from your mother that you go to cram school every day.

245
00:14:55,695 --> 00:14:59,132
You're doing your best. >> Well...｡

246
00:14:59,199 --> 00:15:02,135
What about that Ryunosuke?

247
00:15:02,202 --> 00:15:07,140
Sorry again...

248
00:15:07,207 --> 00:15:09,643
(Luna) Please wait.

249
00:15:09,709 --> 00:15:11,645
Professor Yoshizawa →

250
00:15:11,711 --> 00:15:14,648
The stuffed animals and meat blocks you mentioned earlier are →

251
00:15:14,714 --> 00:15:16,650
How big was it?

252
00:15:16,716 --> 00:15:20,153
How many were there?

253
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:22,656
>> All of them are small.

254
00:15:22,722 --> 00:15:25,659
There are about 10 stuffed animals.

255
00:15:25,725 --> 00:15:28,161
There was also a bag full of meat at the supermarket.

256
00:15:28,228 --> 00:15:32,666
I think there were 7 or 8 rolls.

257
00:15:32,732 --> 00:15:36,236
(Ryoko) There are so many things that are the same.

258
00:15:37,737 --> 00:15:47,180
♪～

259
00:15:47,247 --> 00:15:48,682
(Luna) 《Fluffy...》

260
00:15:48,748 --> 00:15:51,751
(Kominato) [Special takoyaki please] (Bubbly) [Fluffy! ]

261
00:15:55,188 --> 00:15:56,623
(Luna) 《Voluntary recall...》

262
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:59,125
>> [There's no octopus in it though] [I'll try again]

263
00:15:59,192 --> 00:16:01,194
(Ryoko) [Voluntary recall]

264
00:16:03,697 --> 00:16:05,632
(Luna) 《Bomb threat...》

265
00:16:05,699 --> 00:16:10,203
(Monitor) [There was eyewitness testimony about the bomb threat the other day]

266
00:16:11,705 --> 00:16:13,640
(Luna) 《Glass in the sandbox...》

267
00:16:13,707 --> 00:16:15,642
(Ryoko) [Dangerous] (Yoshizawa) [Police patrol the neighborhood →

268
00:16:15,709 --> 00:16:18,712
He has strengthened me.] (Satsuki) [He was my best friend]

269
00:16:22,716 --> 00:16:24,718
(Luna) We are connected.

270
00:16:32,726 --> 00:16:34,661
(Luna) Koji-san →

271
00:16:34,728 --> 00:16:37,731
Let's go to Ryunosuke-san's place together.

272
00:16:48,842 --> 00:16:50,477
(Ryoko) Koji-kun?

273
00:16:50,543 --> 00:16:54,414
>> Ah, too... I haven't seen him for about two years →

274
00:16:54,481 --> 00:16:56,483
Something's making me nervous.

275
00:16:59,753 --> 00:17:03,390
(Luna) Well, for now, we'll go first.

276
00:17:03,456 --> 00:17:07,460
Please come in when you feel ready.

277
00:17:10,463 --> 00:17:12,899
(knock)

278
00:17:12,966 --> 00:17:15,402
(Luna) This is Nomiya.

279
00:17:15,468 --> 00:17:17,971
(sound of door opening)

280
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:24,411
(Luna) Koji-san is also coming.

281
00:17:24,477 --> 00:17:25,912
>> Huh?

282
00:17:25,979 --> 00:17:31,918
(Luna) It seems that she is a good friend of mine who helped me when I first came to Japan.

283
00:17:31,985 --> 00:17:36,923
>> That's not true, Igaguri, we're not really good friends now.

284
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:42,929
(Luna) I wonder if the two of them are as close as Giovanni and Campanella.

285
00:17:42,996 --> 00:17:44,931
>>It's completely different.

286
00:17:44,998 --> 00:17:47,934
I can't do someone like Campanella.

287
00:17:48,001 --> 00:17:49,436
(Ryoko) Huh?

288
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:53,440
(Luna) A character that appears in "Night on the Galactic Railway."

289
00:17:53,506 --> 00:17:57,444
Ryunosuke-san, you really like literature.

290
00:17:57,510 --> 00:18:00,947
(Ryoko) I know the title, but what kind of story is it?

291
00:18:01,014 --> 00:18:03,450
(Luna) Left by Kenji Miyazawa→

292
00:18:03,516 --> 00:18:06,953
A story that asks the question of ``true happiness.''

293
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:10,457
Giovanni, a lonely boy.

294
00:18:10,523 --> 00:18:15,462
On the night of the star festival, he was looking at the sky alone on a hill outside of town.

295
00:18:15,528 --> 00:18:20,467
Before I knew it, I was on board the Galaxy Express, which was traveling through space.

296
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:24,471
My estranged friend Campanella was also there →

297
00:18:24,537 --> 00:18:26,973
As the two of them cross the stars →

298
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:30,477
I repeatedly meet and part with various people.

299
00:18:30,543 --> 00:18:33,980
Giovanni regains his friendship with Campanella.

300
00:18:34,047 --> 00:18:37,484
When the trip suddenly ended and I returned to reality →

301
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:42,055
Then I had to face the sad truth.

302
00:18:43,556 --> 00:18:46,993
>>I have no sympathy for Giovanni or Campanella.

303
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:48,995
I don't like the theme either.

304
00:18:49,062 --> 00:18:52,999
(Luna) I think there are many different interpretations of literature.

305
00:18:53,066 --> 00:18:56,436
Now let's get to the main topic.

306
00:18:56,503 --> 00:18:58,938
Excuse me.

307
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:00,940
Ryunosuke-san→

308
00:19:01,007 --> 00:19:06,946
Did you go out the night there was a bomb threat in the park?

309
00:19:07,013 --> 00:19:10,450
>> Do you think I'm a criminal?

310
00:19:10,517 --> 00:19:13,953
(Luna) At least you're involved →

311
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:15,955
I think there is no doubt.

312
00:19:16,022 --> 00:19:17,957
>> I don't know what the motive is?

313
00:19:18,024 --> 00:19:21,461
(Luna) I understand. >> How?

314
00:19:21,528 --> 00:19:24,464
(Luna) Of course, with the help of literature.

315
00:19:24,531 --> 00:19:29,969
If I were to write a novel, it would unfold like this.

316
00:19:30,036 --> 00:19:34,474
(Luna's voice) Ryunosuke-san has the same stuffed animals and blocks of meat →

317
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:36,976
I gathered up some rolls.

318
00:19:37,043 --> 00:19:41,481
These three have something in common.

319
00:19:41,548 --> 00:19:46,486
Ryoko Do you understand? (Ryoko) Huh? What do we have in common?

320
00:19:46,553 --> 00:19:50,490
It's not the size, right? It's not even a shape...

321
00:19:50,557 --> 00:19:53,493
Oh, are they all soft?

322
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:55,428
(Luna) Thank you for your understanding.

323
00:19:55,495 --> 00:19:59,933
Next, let's talk about the bomb threat incident.

324
00:19:59,999 --> 00:20:03,436
What happened when that happened?

325
00:20:03,503 --> 00:20:07,941
(Ryoko) A piece of glass was found buried in the sandbox.

326
00:20:08,007 --> 00:20:09,442
(Luna) Yes.

327
00:20:09,509 --> 00:20:11,945
(Luna's voice) Because there was a bomb threat→

328
00:20:12,011 --> 00:20:15,949
Neighboring parks were thoroughly investigated.

329
00:20:16,015 --> 00:20:18,451
(Officer) [Suspicious object found! ]

330
00:20:18,518 --> 00:20:21,454
(Luna's voice) Perhaps the sand in the park has been replaced →

331
00:20:21,521 --> 00:20:24,958
Patrols have been stepped up since then.

332
00:20:25,024 --> 00:20:27,026
>> [Sorry] [Yes]

333
00:20:28,528 --> 00:20:31,464
(Luna) Now let's get back to the topic of hoarding.

334
00:20:31,531 --> 00:20:35,468
It seems that Ryunosuke threw them all away.

335
00:20:35,535 --> 00:20:37,971
And as soon as I got it.

336
00:20:38,037 --> 00:20:42,475
(Ryoko) What? Does that mean you bought it specifically to throw it away?

337
00:20:42,542 --> 00:20:44,477
(Luna) That's what it is.

338
00:20:44,544 --> 00:20:47,480
Another customer bought the bread first, so →

339
00:20:47,547 --> 00:20:49,482
I had no choice but to snatch it.

340
00:20:49,549 --> 00:20:53,987
Mr. Ango Sakaguchi's "Meiji Kaika Ango Torimonocho" →

341
00:20:54,053 --> 00:20:57,423
In order to protect a family secret in a work called ...→

342
00:20:57,490 --> 00:21:00,426
There are ways to cover up sin with sin.

343
00:21:00,493 --> 00:21:05,431
Ryunosuke also did the snatching to cover up another crime.

344
00:21:05,498 --> 00:21:08,001
The same goes for bomb threats.

345
00:21:09,502 --> 00:21:11,504
(Ryoko) What do you mean?

346
00:21:12,505 --> 00:21:14,941
(Luna's voice) In the soft sand of the park→

347
00:21:15,008 --> 00:21:17,944
There were pieces of glass embedded in it.

348
00:21:18,011 --> 00:21:21,948
All the things I bought up and threw away are soft.

349
00:21:22,015 --> 00:21:24,450
That means...

350
00:21:24,517 --> 00:21:25,952
(Ryoko) Ah!

351
00:21:26,019 --> 00:21:31,457
Was there something embedded inside the stuffed animals and food?

352
00:21:31,524 --> 00:21:35,528
(Luna) Yes, there is something very dangerous.

353
00:21:37,030 --> 00:21:43,536
(Ryoko) But why would you bury something inside and then collect it yourself and dispose of it?

354
00:21:44,537 --> 00:21:48,975
Ah! Maybe...

355
00:21:49,042 --> 00:21:50,977
(Luna) Yes.

356
00:21:51,044 --> 00:21:53,479
Ryunosuke wasn't the one who planted it.

357
00:21:53,546 --> 00:21:55,915
Witness someone preparing →

358
00:21:55,982 --> 00:22:00,420
I collected it to prevent it from falling into the hands of others.

359
00:22:00,486 --> 00:22:02,922
I bought all the same things →

360
00:22:02,989 --> 00:22:06,492
I couldn't tell which one was in there.

361
00:22:12,498 --> 00:22:19,005
(Luna) And the person that Ryunosuke-san went so far to break his heart with was...

362
00:22:29,515 --> 00:22:33,453
(Luna) When Kouji saw the police coming, he realized what he had done→

363
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:37,457
I was worried that I might have gotten Ryunosuke involved.→

364
00:22:37,523 --> 00:22:39,525
You came to visit me, right?

365
00:22:51,037 --> 00:22:53,539
(Luna) Can you talk to me?

366
00:22:58,811 --> 00:23:01,314
(Luna) Can you talk to me?

367
00:23:04,817 --> 00:23:08,821
>> Studying is... hard...

368
00:23:10,323 --> 00:23:13,259
(Koji) At my preparatory school→

369
00:23:13,326 --> 00:23:18,264
The level is so high that I can't keep up with the class...

370
00:23:18,331 --> 00:23:20,833
I don't have any friends I can talk to.

371
00:23:22,835 --> 00:23:28,775
I'm worried every day if I fail the internal entrance exam...

372
00:23:28,841 --> 00:23:31,711
The night I got a bad grade on a mock exam at cram school →

373
00:23:31,778 --> 00:23:34,714
When you stop by a shopping center →

374
00:23:34,781 --> 00:23:36,716
They sell needles...

375
00:23:36,783 --> 00:23:48,227
♪～

376
00:23:48,294 --> 00:23:51,731
(Kouji's voice) Just when you think you've done something you should never do →

377
00:23:51,798 --> 00:23:54,801
My heart is pounding...

378
00:23:58,805 --> 00:24:01,741
(Koji's voice) I thought I'd never do it again→

379
00:24:01,808 --> 00:24:06,312
When I remember the thrill of that time, I want to do it again...

380
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:19,325
(Luna) Ryunosuke-san witnessed it.

381
00:24:23,329 --> 00:24:28,334
>> I was wandering around at night when I saw Kouji.

382
00:24:37,777 --> 00:24:40,713
[Ah, bear! ]

383
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:42,782
(Ryuunosuke) [Sorry]

384
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:55,228
(Ryuunosuke's voice) After that, I ambushed him every day and followed him.

385
00:24:55,294 --> 00:25:12,245
♪～

386
00:25:12,311 --> 00:25:14,247
[Sound of needle hitting]

387
00:25:14,313 --> 00:25:24,757
♪～

388
00:25:24,824 --> 00:25:28,261
There was a strange noise that night.

389
00:25:28,327 --> 00:25:30,263
[Gashan]

390
00:25:30,329 --> 00:25:34,834
[Gasha Gasha…]

391
00:25:37,837 --> 00:25:39,839
[Sound of glass breaking]

392
00:25:44,343 --> 00:25:46,279
[Sound of glass shards being inserted]

393
00:25:46,345 --> 00:26:12,805
♪～

394
00:26:12,872 --> 00:26:15,808
(Ryuunosuke's voice) It's impossible to keep watch every day →

395
00:26:15,875 --> 00:26:20,379
I don't know what I'll do if this continues to escalate.

396
00:26:26,886 --> 00:26:29,889
☏ [Is it an incident? Was it an accident? ]

397
00:26:31,324 --> 00:26:34,827
[I planted a bomb in the park]

398
00:26:36,829 --> 00:26:40,766
(Ryuunosuke's voice) Now that I think about it, I thought there would be more patrols.

399
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:44,770
Then I wouldn't be able to do anything weird.

400
00:26:44,837 --> 00:26:48,774
But why did Kouji do that?

401
00:26:48,841 --> 00:26:51,777
I don't know why.

402
00:26:51,844 --> 00:26:56,282
Then, my sister said that she would solve mysteries through literature.→

403
00:26:56,349 --> 00:26:59,352
Maybe I'll know something.

404
00:27:01,354 --> 00:27:03,789
When did you realize?

405
00:27:03,856 --> 00:27:08,794
(Luna) I'm convinced that Ryunosuke hasn't seen him for a long time →

406
00:27:08,861 --> 00:27:11,797
When I knew Koji-san's hairstyle.

407
00:27:11,864 --> 00:27:15,868
>> [That's not true, Igaguri, we're not really good friends now]

408
00:27:21,374 --> 00:27:25,811
(Ryoko) Why did the distance between the two grow?

409
00:27:25,878 --> 00:27:29,315
Is it because we went to different schools?

410
00:27:29,382 --> 00:27:32,251
>>I hate this guy.

411
00:27:32,318 --> 00:27:35,254
I didn't want to see your face.

412
00:27:35,321 --> 00:27:39,258
(Luna) Kouji-san stopped the dance we were working hard on together→

413
00:27:39,325 --> 00:27:41,827
I felt abandoned.

414
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:46,265
>> That's not my intention...

415
00:27:46,332 --> 00:27:48,768
What is dance? That's what it feels like.

416
00:27:48,834 --> 00:27:53,272
If this guy invites you, you'll want to do it and do your best.

417
00:27:53,339 --> 00:27:57,276
But in the end it was all in vain.

418
00:27:57,343 --> 00:28:01,847
(Luna) Then why did you help Koji-san?

419
00:28:03,849 --> 00:28:06,786
Isn't it because it was important?

420
00:28:06,852 --> 00:28:11,357
The dancing and the time I spent with Kouji.

421
00:28:13,859 --> 00:28:18,798
There are dreams that can never come true no matter how much you wish for them.

422
00:28:18,864 --> 00:28:22,301
I have it too.

423
00:28:22,368 --> 00:28:27,807
But the time I spent dreaming of something →

424
00:28:27,873 --> 00:28:30,743
The time I suffered →

425
00:28:30,810 --> 00:28:35,314
All of that makes you who you are today.

426
00:28:40,319 --> 00:28:44,757
(Luna) So please don't deny your past self.

427
00:28:44,824 --> 00:28:50,830
Also about the friends I spent those precious moments with.

428
00:28:52,331 --> 00:28:55,768
Even now that we're estranged, I can't leave you alone →

429
00:28:55,835 --> 00:28:59,271
You tried to save him.

430
00:28:59,338 --> 00:29:04,343
It's a miracle that I was able to meet a friend who makes me feel that way.

431
00:29:05,845 --> 00:29:10,282
>>Ryuunosuke, I'm sorry.

432
00:29:10,349 --> 00:29:12,852
sorry….

433
00:29:16,856 --> 00:29:20,159
(Luna) But that doesn't mean what you guys did→

434
00:29:20,226 --> 00:29:23,662
That's never allowed.

435
00:29:23,729 --> 00:29:26,665
Not only did it terrify the world.

436
00:29:26,732 --> 00:29:31,670
There was a possibility of injuring someone or even threatening their life.

437
00:29:36,175 --> 00:29:43,115
(Luna) Koji-san, your problematic behavior is all an SOS from your heart.

438
00:29:43,182 --> 00:29:48,120
We will introduce you to a lawyer who is knowledgeable about such youth issues.

439
00:29:48,187 --> 00:29:53,626
He is my cousin and is a very talented and trustworthy person.

440
00:29:53,692 --> 00:29:59,632
Please talk with your parents and work on your mental health care.

441
00:29:59,698 --> 00:30:01,700
>> Yes.

442
00:30:04,203 --> 00:30:07,139
I'm going to the police too.

443
00:30:07,206 --> 00:30:09,141
I'm sure you'll get arrested, right?

444
00:30:09,208 --> 00:30:11,143
(Luna) That's right.

445
00:30:11,210 --> 00:30:16,649
Even though you were trying to protect him, you made a mistake.

446
00:30:16,715 --> 00:30:19,151
Sin is sin.

447
00:30:19,218 --> 00:30:37,102
♪～

448
00:30:37,169 --> 00:30:39,605
>> Thank you very much.

449
00:30:39,672 --> 00:30:44,109
I'm really sorry for causing you trouble.

450
00:30:44,176 --> 00:30:45,678
(Luna) No.

451
00:30:52,184 --> 00:30:55,187
(Ryoko) Ah... then.

452
00:31:00,192 --> 00:31:04,630
(Ryoko) I lied to Satsuki.

453
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:06,699
22 years ago.

454
00:31:10,202 --> 00:31:14,139
(Ryoko) I lied to Satsuki.

455
00:31:14,773 --> 00:31:17,209
22 years ago.

456
00:31:18,143 --> 00:31:21,647
(Satsuki) [Ryoko: It's okay, you'll definitely recover]

457
00:31:27,152 --> 00:31:30,589
(Ryoko) [Enough] >> [Eh? ]

458
00:31:30,656 --> 00:31:36,662
(Ryoko) [Something... it doesn't really matter anymore]

459
00:31:38,163 --> 00:31:42,101
[Huh~]

460
00:31:42,167 --> 00:31:45,104
[Sorry, Satsuki]

461
00:31:45,170 --> 00:31:47,673
[I quit playing]

462
00:31:49,174 --> 00:31:51,110
>> [Ryoko…]

463
00:31:51,176 --> 00:31:53,178
(Ryoko) [Huh...]

464
00:31:54,179 --> 00:31:57,116
(Luna) I didn't want to make him wait until his injury healed.

465
00:31:57,182 --> 00:31:59,118
A gentle lie.

466
00:31:59,184 --> 00:32:01,687
I'm with Kazuto.

467
00:32:04,189 --> 00:32:09,628
(Ryoko) After that, Satsuki paired up with another athlete and won a medal.

468
00:32:10,262 --> 00:32:13,198
I was so happy.

469
00:32:13,265 --> 00:32:17,202
But I was also jealous.

470
00:32:18,704 --> 00:32:25,644
I still feel regretful and wish I hadn't quit.

471
00:32:25,711 --> 00:32:30,716
The glittering Satsuki is so bright that it hurts...

472
00:32:32,217 --> 00:32:39,158
Since then, badminton has been sealed deep in my heart.

473
00:32:39,224 --> 00:32:44,663
But Satsuki is also a lot of things.

474
00:32:44,730 --> 00:32:48,734
It can be difficult and painful.

475
00:32:51,236 --> 00:32:54,673
(Luna) I think Satsuki-san noticed it.

476
00:32:54,740 --> 00:32:57,676
Ryoko was lying.

477
00:32:57,743 --> 00:33:00,179
We have been a pair for many years →

478
00:33:00,245 --> 00:33:03,248
There's no way you wouldn't notice something like that.

479
00:33:05,250 --> 00:33:09,688
Both Ryoko and Satsuki were clumsy.

480
00:33:09,755 --> 00:33:12,257
Ryunosuke too.

481
00:33:19,264 --> 00:33:23,702
(Luna) Huh? Mr. Tamura caught that serial arsonist?

482
00:33:23,769 --> 00:33:26,205
>>The stakeout was very persistent.

483
00:33:26,271 --> 00:33:29,708
(Luna) Thank you for your hard work. Looks like we'll be able to do well here.

484
00:33:29,775 --> 00:33:31,710
(Tamura) Well, I'll do my best.

485
00:33:31,777 --> 00:33:33,712
What happened to that? password.

486
00:33:33,779 --> 00:33:36,715
(Luna) I looked through the book I borrowed →

487
00:33:36,782 --> 00:33:39,218
There was nothing that could be a clue.

488
00:33:39,284 --> 00:33:43,222
I'm sorry that I asked Ryoko to go out with me.

489
00:33:43,288 --> 00:33:46,725
>> If there is a sick child in the east, go and take care of it →

490
00:33:46,792 --> 00:33:51,230
If my mother is tired in the west, she will go and carry the bundle of rice.

491
00:33:51,296 --> 00:33:53,732
(Luna) It's ``Ame Nimo Makezu.''

492
00:33:53,799 --> 00:33:57,236
>> Something sounds like Luna.

493
00:33:57,302 --> 00:34:01,240
(Luna) I wish I could become like that.

494
00:34:01,306 --> 00:34:03,776
(Tamura) Kominato-san, when did you become a literary character?

495
00:34:03,842 --> 00:34:06,278
(clicks tongue) That's annoying.

496
00:34:06,345 --> 00:34:08,781
You should go home now. It's closed.

497
00:34:08,847 --> 00:34:11,283
(Tamura) Please drink it on the day you get credit.

498
00:34:11,350 --> 00:34:13,786
>> You must be drinking every day. (Tamura) Hey... just one more drink.

499
00:34:13,852 --> 00:35:04,837
♪～

500
00:35:09,341 --> 00:35:13,278
(Ryoko) Ah, good morning, aroma. >> Good morning.

501
00:35:13,745 --> 00:35:16,181
(Atsushi) Why are you standing there?

502
00:35:16,248 --> 00:35:18,684
(fragrance) I have a story.

503
00:35:20,185 --> 00:35:22,187
(Ryoko) Why don't you sit down?

504
00:35:30,696 --> 00:35:32,698
>> What happened?

505
00:35:35,701 --> 00:35:41,139
I... I want to go to voice acting school...

506
00:35:41,206 --> 00:35:43,208
Huh? (Ryoko) Huh?

507
00:35:45,210 --> 00:35:47,412
>>I want to go to voice acting school.

508
00:35:47,479 --> 00:35:49,548
voice actor?

509
00:35:49,615 --> 00:35:52,484
I started working part-time so I could save my own money.

510
00:35:52,551 --> 00:35:56,989
I feel bad that I was able to get into the university, but...

511
00:35:57,055 --> 00:36:00,492
No no, what are you talking about, voice actors?

512
00:36:00,559 --> 00:36:02,995
(Ryoko) Why didn't you say that first?

513
00:36:03,462 --> 00:36:05,397
>> Huh?

514
00:36:05,464 --> 00:36:09,034
(Ryoko) I don't want to quit university, I want to become a voice actor →

515
00:36:09,101 --> 00:36:12,037
I wish you had said that from the beginning.

516
00:36:12,104 --> 00:36:15,541
>> I thought they would make fun of me for not being able to get used to it.

517
00:36:15,607 --> 00:36:17,976
(Ryoko) Why do you decide?

518
00:36:18,043 --> 00:36:20,479
That's not true, right?

519
00:36:20,546 --> 00:36:24,483
>> Ah… no, ah…｡

520
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:29,788
(Ryoko) Thank you for talking to me.

521
00:36:29,855 --> 00:36:31,390
>> But that kind of world →

522
00:36:31,456 --> 00:36:34,393
It's unstable, it's tough, and it's not easy.

523
00:36:34,459 --> 00:36:37,963
I know, but...

524
00:36:44,469 --> 00:36:47,406
(Ryoko) Ah, this is...

525
00:36:47,472 --> 00:36:50,976
(Yoshika) Your father wrote this article, right?

526
00:36:52,978 --> 00:36:55,914
I want to do my best too.

527
00:36:55,981 --> 00:36:59,418
I found what I want to do.

528
00:36:59,484 --> 00:37:06,925
I wish I could entertain someone with my voice.

529
00:37:06,992 --> 00:37:13,065
I know it's hard, but...→

530
00:37:13,131 --> 00:37:15,634
I want to take on the challenge.

531
00:37:19,805 --> 00:37:23,742
(Ryoko) This is a good article.

532
00:37:23,809 --> 00:37:26,745
No matter what the outcome →

533
00:37:26,812 --> 00:37:31,316
I think the time you spend immersed in what you want to do is a treasure.

534
00:37:33,318 --> 00:37:37,255
Mom finally noticed.

535
00:37:37,923 --> 00:37:42,427
I started to feel proud of that time.

536
00:37:43,929 --> 00:37:49,935
Because it was who I was then that made me who I am now.

537
00:37:57,442 --> 00:38:02,381
(Ryoko) I want Yoshika to do what she likes to the fullest.

538
00:38:02,447 --> 00:38:04,950
Don't regret it.

539
00:38:10,956 --> 00:38:15,460
>> Please let me do it, please.

540
00:38:20,899 --> 00:38:22,868
There are conditions.

541
00:38:22,934 --> 00:38:25,871
Graduate from university properly.

542
00:38:26,838 --> 00:38:28,473
Eh...｡

543
00:38:28,540 --> 00:38:34,980
(Ryoko) Then you should go to double school at university and a voice acting school.

544
00:38:35,047 --> 00:38:37,315
>>That's cool.

545
00:38:37,382 --> 00:38:40,318
(Kikuo) I think it's quite tough.

546
00:38:40,385 --> 00:38:44,389
Are you okay! I'll definitely do my best!

547
00:38:46,958 --> 00:38:48,960
thank you.

548
00:38:52,431 --> 00:38:55,934
(Ryoko) Good luck. I'll support you.

549
00:39:01,940 --> 00:39:04,376
(Luna) Yoshika-san, that was great.

550
00:39:04,443 --> 00:39:07,879
I think it's really reassuring to have your parents supporting you.

551
00:39:07,946 --> 00:39:09,881
I'm jealous.

552
00:39:09,948 --> 00:39:12,884
(Ryoko) Thank you. Maybe it's because of mom.

553
00:39:12,951 --> 00:39:14,886
(Luna) I don't have anything.

554
00:39:14,953 --> 00:39:20,325
Ah, yesterday I went to Professor Yoshizawa's house to return the book I had borrowed.

555
00:39:20,392 --> 00:39:22,327
I also met Satsuki →

556
00:39:22,394 --> 00:39:24,329
I asked about Ryunosuke and his friends.

557
00:39:24,396 --> 00:39:26,832
(Ryoko) Well, what happened?

558
00:39:26,898 --> 00:39:31,336
(Luna) Both of them will probably be sentenced to probation.

559
00:39:31,403 --> 00:39:33,338
There were no victims →

560
00:39:33,405 --> 00:39:36,842
Because the individuals themselves are deeply remorseful →

561
00:39:36,908 --> 00:39:39,344
It seems likely that the circumstances will be met with extenuating circumstances.

562
00:39:39,411 --> 00:39:42,347
(Ryoko) Huh~ Good.

563
00:39:42,414 --> 00:39:46,852
(Luna) Satsuki-san, you served me that delicious madeleine again.

564
00:39:46,918 --> 00:39:50,856
He said it tasted like memories. (Ryoko) Yeah...｡

565
00:39:50,922 --> 00:39:54,926
I noticed it as soon as I took a bite the other day.

566
00:39:57,429 --> 00:40:01,366
At Madeleine, a pastry shop near the high school.

567
00:40:01,433 --> 00:40:05,871
We always ate together after practice.

568
00:40:05,937 --> 00:40:08,440
It was nostalgic.

569
00:40:10,442 --> 00:40:15,380
(Luna) In Proust's work ``In Search of Lost Time'' →

570
00:40:15,447 --> 00:40:18,316
While eating madeleines soaked in tea →

571
00:40:18,383 --> 00:40:21,820
There is a famous scene that brings back memories of the past.

572
00:40:21,887 --> 00:40:25,323
Every time Satsuki buys that madeleine →

573
00:40:25,390 --> 00:40:28,393
You might have remembered Ryoko.

574
00:40:30,395 --> 00:40:33,832
(Ryoko) Mom is so kind.

575
00:40:33,899 --> 00:40:37,836
I just get it.

576
00:40:37,903 --> 00:40:39,838
(Luna) That's not true.

577
00:40:39,905 --> 00:40:41,339
(Ryoko) Yes.

578
00:40:41,406 --> 00:40:45,844
That's why I wanted to be of some help to moms, too.

579
00:40:45,911 --> 00:40:47,846
I thought about a lot of things.

580
00:40:47,913 --> 00:40:51,850
(Luna) What? (Ryoko) Password hint.

581
00:40:51,917 --> 00:40:56,855
You told me about the site of Natsume Soseki's former residence the other day, right?

582
00:40:56,922 --> 00:41:00,425
So I did a little research.

583
00:41:03,995 --> 00:41:07,999
(Ryoko) At this place, Soseki said ``I am a cat.'' →

584
00:41:08,066 --> 00:41:10,502
You wrote it, right? (Luna) Yeah.

585
00:41:10,569 --> 00:41:12,504
(Ryoko) Maybe the password is →

586
00:41:12,571 --> 00:41:16,575
I guess it's the place where the story was born.

587
00:41:18,076 --> 00:41:22,514
Look, the address is written here, right?

588
00:41:22,581 --> 00:41:27,018
(Luna) "Sendagicho 57".

589
00:41:27,085 --> 00:41:32,023
Ah, but the password must be more than 4 digits.

590
00:41:32,090 --> 00:41:36,094
(Ryoko) But what if we combined Sendagi's "thousand"?

591
00:41:38,096 --> 00:41:40,098
(Luna) It might be possible.

592
00:41:47,606 --> 00:41:54,112
(Luna) 1000 and 57. (Sound of keyboard hitting)

593
00:41:55,614 --> 00:41:57,048
(Monitor) (Error sound)

594
00:41:57,115 --> 00:42:00,986
(Ryoko) Oh, no... I'm sorry.

595
00:42:01,052 --> 00:42:04,556
(Luna) No, there are still three more chances.

596
00:42:17,569 --> 00:42:20,005
(Luna) Okay, I'll go in a bit.

597
00:42:20,071 --> 00:42:23,008
(Ryoko) Where? (Luna) Shuzenji Onsen.

598
00:42:23,074 --> 00:42:27,012
Shuzenji is the place where Natsume Sensei visited for medical treatment.

599
00:42:27,078 --> 00:42:31,082
The shop is closed today, so I'm going to reset things a bit.

600
00:42:34,085 --> 00:42:38,023
(Luna) That's right, this.

601
00:42:38,089 --> 00:42:40,525
From Satsuki-san.

602
00:42:40,592 --> 00:42:42,527
Her cell phone number.

603
00:42:42,594 --> 00:42:44,596
(Ryoko) Huh...｡

604
00:42:50,602 --> 00:42:53,538
(Ryoko) ⟨Mom said⟩

605
00:42:53,605 --> 00:42:59,044
⟨It's a miracle to be able to meet a friend who is important to you⟩

606
00:43:24,569 --> 00:43:31,009
♪～

607
00:43:31,076 --> 00:43:33,011
(Satsuki) [Thank you for waiting~]

608
00:43:33,078 --> 00:43:36,014
(Satsuki: Ryoko) [I'll take it. Hmm! ]

609
00:43:36,081 --> 00:43:37,515
(Ryoko) [Last 1 Morai]

610
00:43:37,582 --> 00:43:40,585
>> [Ah, I was thinking of eating it]

611
00:43:42,587 --> 00:43:45,023
(Satsuki) [Sha! ] (Ryoko) [Satsuki Nice! ]

612
00:43:45,090 --> 00:43:48,026
[Let's definitely win] >> [Of course]

613
00:43:48,093 --> 00:43:50,028
[If it's me and Ryoko, we'll definitely win]

614
00:43:50,095 --> 00:43:52,030
(Ryoko) [Let's do our best tomorrow too! 〕 >> 〔I'll do my best! ]

615
00:43:52,097 --> 00:43:54,032
〔laughter〕

616
00:43:54,099 --> 00:44:07,479
♪～

617
00:44:07,545 --> 00:44:11,483
(Ryoko) ⟨Mom and Satsuki are my miracles⟩

618
00:44:11,549 --> 00:44:17,989
♪～

619
00:44:18,056 --> 00:44:29,000
📱(vibration sound)

620
00:44:29,067 --> 00:44:30,502
(Luna) Mom?

621
00:44:30,568 --> 00:44:32,504
📱(Misato) Hey, where are you now?

622
00:44:32,570 --> 00:44:34,005
(Luna) Huh?

623
00:44:34,072 --> 00:44:39,010
(Misato) Please help me, come right away!

624
00:44:39,077 --> 00:44:42,013
(Luna) What? what happened?

625
00:44:42,080 --> 00:44:44,082
mother?
